          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0659P0-04064'>
        <a name='S5LV0659P0_20040323_GCR_56'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-michael-morris-1' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040323_GCR_56' title='Link to this speech by Mr Michael Morris' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-michael-morris-1" title="Mr Michael Morris">Lord Naseby</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            There is just one point I wish to raise. Let us assume for a moment that the mother is 14 and therefore is some way off from being 16. Let us also assume that it takes some time to find a responsible person. What is the position of the child when the voucher is eventually issued? Is it backdated to the birth of the child or is the operational date that at which one has discovered who will vouch for the child?
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0659P0-04065'>
        <a name='S5LV0659P0_20040323_GCR_57'>  </a>
